claim: In 2015 , the film Jurassic World generated $ 1.6 billion in total revenue at the box office .
truth: After a record-breaking opening weekend during which it grossed $ 500 million worldwide , Jurassic World generated a total of $ 1.6 billion in box office revenue , standing as the fourth highest-grossing film of all time without inflation adjustment , as well as the second highest-grossing film of 2015 and the highest-grossing film in the franchise .

claim: Ansah ranked second in NFL in sacks with less than 14 points in 2015 .
truth: During the 2015 season , Ansah is currently ranked second in the NFL in sacks with 13.5 and trails only Oakland 's Khalil Mack by 1.5 for the league lead .

claim: Brooks has sold more than 170 million records worldwide .
truth: His most recent album , Gunslinger , was released in November 2016.Brooks is also one of the world 's best-selling music artists , having sold more than 170 million records .

claim: China has less than 24,575 cases of coronavirus as of February 5 , 2020 .
truth: As of 5 February 2020 , approximately 24,569 cases have been confirmed , including in every province-level division of China .

claim: After April 2017 , Baby by Justin Bieber had over 1.60 billion views on YouTube .
truth: On March 5 , 2014 , `` Baby '' became the second video , after `` Gangnam Style '' , to receive 1 billion views on YouTube , and is the nineteenth most viewed video on the site , with over 1.60 billion views as of May 2017 .

claim: The motion picture Traffic was released in 2001 and features a fight between the Juárez Cartel and the Tijuana Cartel .
truth: Some US sources estimate the cartel 's income reached as high as $ 200 million a week under former boss Amado Carrillo Fuentes , who mysteriously died in July 1997.A look inside a giant drug cartel , Christian Science Monitor , 1999 The Juárez Cartel was featured battling the rival Tijuana Cartel in the 2001 motion picture Traffic .

claim: China had less than 9,940 coronavirus cases by January 31 , 2020 .
truth: As of 31 January 2020 , approximately 9,934 cases have been confirmed , including in every province-level division of China .

claim: There were fewer than 396,000 coronavirus cases and under 104,000 recoveries by March 24 .
truth: As of 24 March , more than 395,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in more than 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 17,200 deaths and more than 103,000 recoveries .

claim: The first cases of the coronavirus pandemic in Lithuania were recorded in March 2020 .
truth: This article documents the impacts of the 2019–20 coronavirus pandemic in Lithuania , and may not include all the contemporary major responses and measures .

claim: The Founder hints that the McDonald brothers should have received under $ 500 million annually , on royalties .
truth: An epilogue reveals that the McDonald brothers were never paid their royalties , which could have been in the area of $ 700 million a year.

claim: There were over 337,000 cases of COVID-19 by March 23 , 2020 .
truth: As of 22 March , more than 335,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 14,600 deaths and 97,000 recoveries .

claim: Pixar denied that it was considering any sequels to Inside Out according to a 2016 interview by president Jim Morris , mainly due to the fact that they are concentrating on new film ideas .
truth: In a July 2016 interview , Pixar president Jim Morris said that while demand for a sequel is high , the company has committed its resources to several original movie concepts from June 7 , 2019 , onward , and that no sequels to any of Pixar 's other films , including Inside Out , were being contemplated at this time.

claim: Less than 317,000 cases of COVID-19 have been confirmed .
truth: As of 22 March , more than 315,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 188 countries and territories , resulting in more than 13,500 deaths and 95,000 recoveries .

claim: There are less than 359,000 cases of COVID-19 as of 23 March .
truth: As of 23 March , more than 358,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 190 countries and territories , resulting in more than 15,400 deaths and over 100,000 recoveries .

claim: The use of the name Delmarva occurred on 10 February 1877 in the Middleton Transcript newspaper in Middleton .
truth: While Delmar was founded and named in 1859 , the earliest uses of the name Delmarva occurred several decades later ( for example on February 10 , 1877 in the Middleton Transcript newspaper in Middleton , DelawareMiddleton Transcript February 10 , 1877 ) and appear to have been commercial ; for example , the Delmarva Heat , Light , and Refrigerating Corp. of Chincoteague , Virginia , was in existence by 1913Annual Report of the Secretary of the Commonwealth to the Governor and General Assembly of Virginia for the Year Ending September 30 , 1914 ( Richmond , Va. , 1915 ) , p. 267.—but general use of the term did not occur until the 1920s .
